In one of the rooms of this hotel,

22:15.584 --> 22:18.712
you will find something that will give
you all the answers that you need.

22:18.879 --> 22:20.870
Of course, you have
to ask the right questions.

22:22.049 --> 22:23.459
NICK:
Which room?

22:23.634 --> 22:26.842
Come on, Nick. That would make it too easy.

22:27.013 --> 22:30.346
Hey, you better hurry.
Round four has already started.

22:35.980 --> 22:38.141
(PANTING)

22:38.315 --> 22:40.306
(BUZZER SOUNDS)

22:40.484 --> 22:42.395
(ELECTRICAL CRACKLING)

22:42.570 --> 22:44.060
(LOCK CLICKS)

22:44.238 --> 22:46.399
(DOOR SQUEAKS OPEN)

22:46.574 --> 22:47.780
Which room? Which room?

22:47.950 --> 22:51.659
Round four. Which room?

22:51.829 --> 22:52.989
MAN:
What's up?

22:53.164 --> 22:55.155
Welcome to the Fortune Palace.
How can I help you?

22:55.332 --> 22:58.824
- Oh, shit! Did someone OD?
- No, no, no. No one OD'd.

22:59.003 --> 23:01.415
- Thank God.
- I'm looking for a room.

23:01.589 --> 23:02.795
You're in luck.
We have those here.

23:02.965 --> 23:06.457
I'm not sure which room I'm looking for,
exactly. Something on the fourth floor?

23:09.472 --> 23:11.463
Fuck. Come on, man.

23:17.730 --> 23:19.220
Sorry, all ocupado.

23:19.398 --> 23:21.263
- All of them?
- Yes.

23:21.442 --> 23:24.184
Listen, it's real important I find out
who's in those rooms on the fourth floor.

23:24.361 --> 23:26.101
- I'm looking for someone.
- Aren't we all.

23:26.280 --> 23:28.441
- Try Match.com.
- Lives are at stake here.

23:28.616 --> 23:30.072
- Call the police.
- I can't do that.

23:30.242 --> 23:33.234
I can't help you.
Have a nice night.

23:37.917 --> 23:39.908
Listen, man, I'm sorry.

23:40.086 --> 23:41.701
(GRUNTS)

23:41.879 --> 23:43.164
- (COUGHS, GRUNTS)
- Sorry.

23:43.339 --> 23:47.332
Keep pressure on it,
it'll stop bleeding in a few minutes.

23:49.720 --> 23:52.097
(SIREN CHIRPS, TIRES SCREECH)

23:52.264 --> 23:54.676
(INDISTINCT RADIO TRANSMISSION)

23:55.518 --> 23:56.758
OFFICER:
Work in a grid!

24:00.314 --> 24:02.600
(CLEARS THROAT)

24:02.775 --> 24:04.185
WOMAN:
What's the urgency?

24:04.360 --> 24:06.942
You know I'm swamped
with the governor's case.

24:07.113 --> 24:09.946
MAN:
Well, I thought it was fairly important.

24:10.116 --> 24:14.234
Uh... Paramedic's name is Jay Thompson.
Still unconscious.

24:14.411 --> 24:17.574
Second-degree burns
and a pretty bad concussion from the blast.

24:17.748 --> 24:19.704
Seriously?
You called me here for this?

24:19.875 --> 24:21.706
You could've handled this on your own.

24:21.877 --> 24:23.287
Well, I thought the same thing,

24:23.462 --> 24:26.044
until they mentioned
the guy's body they found inside.

24:26.215 --> 24:28.752
Initial sweep also picked up traces of C-4.

24:29.385 --> 24:31.376
WOMAN:
All right. Well, you got my attention.

24:31.554 --> 24:35.046
- Paramedic's partner is missing.
- Missing, huh?

24:35.224 --> 24:38.011
Yeah, the name is Nick Malloy.

24:38.894 --> 24:42.227
Homeland Security's gonna be
all over this once word of the C-4 hits.

24:42.398 --> 24:44.059
Well, then slow it down.

24:46.652 --> 24:50.770
Get the geek squad down here.
I want to know what that saw.

24:50.948 --> 24:53.030
(BEEPING)

24:53.200 --> 24:55.407
Nobody saw that?

24:55.578 --> 24:57.443
(PHONE RlNGlNG)

24:57.621 --> 24:59.657
McKenzie.

24:59.832 --> 25:02.073
Have you tracked down Governor Devlin?

25:02.251 --> 25:04.583
(HELICOPTER FLYING OVERHEAD)

25:07.047 --> 25:08.548
Round four.

25:08.716 --> 25:11.708
(DISTANT, INDISTINCT VOICES)

25:17.725 --> 25:19.306
Four-six, four-three.

25:23.355 --> 25:25.391
Forty-four.

25:25.566 --> 25:28.649
(WOMAN MOANING)

25:28.819 --> 25:31.026
(MAN MOANING)

25:31.197 --> 25:33.358
(LOUD SLAP)

25:34.033 --> 25:36.319
(SULTRY MUSIC PLAYS)

25:54.803 --> 25:57.340
(MUTTERS)

25:57.514 --> 25:59.095
(WOMAN GASPS)

25:59.266 --> 26:02.178
Hey, dude, what the hell?
Can't you read the sign?

26:02.353 --> 26:04.389
NICK:
Who is he?

26:04.563 --> 26:06.599
The guy on the phone!
What does he want?

26:06.774 --> 26:09.607
- Easy, easy, man. All right?
- Who is he?

26:09.777 --> 26:12.143
Uh, I have no idea
what you're talking about, man.

26:12.321 --> 26:13.857
(PANTING)

26:15.532 --> 26:17.523
He said the answers would be here.
They got to be here.

26:17.701 --> 26:19.532
- WOMAN: Tommy, get up.
- Shut up.

26:19.703 --> 26:22.285
- Get him out of here.
- They got to be here. Where are they?

26:22.456 --> 26:25.619
- Now I'm making you leave, OK, man?
- Is that right?

26:25.793 --> 26:27.954
Yeah, that's right.

26:29.588 --> 26:32.330
- (WOMAN SNICKERS)
- (CHUCKLES)

26:34.635 --> 26:35.920
(CHOKING) That hurt.

26:36.095 --> 26:39.337
- Where is it? Where is it?!
- Get off him! Let go of him!

26:39.515 --> 26:42.848
- What? Piece of shit.
- Get off of him!

26:43.018 --> 26:44.269
Get off of him!

26:46.355 --> 26:49.062
- Come here.
- WOMAN: Oh, my God. Oh, my God!

26:49.233 --> 26:50.643
- Tommy!
- (TOMMY MOANS)

26:50.818 --> 26:53.355
- Stay put!
- Hey, I'm right here!

26:53.529 --> 26:55.235
(TOMMY GROANS)

26:57.533 --> 26:59.740
- Are you part of this?
- Part of What?

26:59.910 --> 27:01.866
- NICK: Are you part of this?!
- Yeah, I'm part of this.

27:02.037 --> 27:04.449
The getaway van's parked out back.

27:04.623 --> 27:06.705
(TOMMY GROANING)

27:08.294 --> 27:11.411
- (WOMAN WHIMPERING)
- Where is it?

27:12.298 --> 27:14.630
- Where...?
- (PHONE RlNGlNG)

27:14.800 --> 27:18.418
Answer it!
Answer the phone!

27:18.595 --> 27:20.176
- NOW, Where is it?
- WOMAN: Hello?

27:20.347 --> 27:21.553
- NICK: Where is it?
- MAN: Where is What?

27:21.724 --> 27:25.262
NICK: If my Wife is hurt, so help me God,
I Will fuck you up hard. Do you hear me?

27:25.436 --> 27:26.721
Hey!

27:26.895 --> 27:28.271
It's for you.

27:30.691 --> 27:32.647
(TOMMY COUGHING)

27:32.818 --> 27:34.979
My God, Tommy!

27:35.154 --> 27:39.397
Hey, congratulations, Nick, you found
the room, but you're making a mess.

27:39.575 --> 27:41.440
I hope you don't expect
me to pay for this.

27:41.618 --> 27:43.233
But did you find the answers?

27:43.412 --> 27:46.028
- There 's nothing here.
- Of course there is, Nick.

27:46.206 --> 27:49.949
NOW, listen to me, when you find it,
bring it With you.

27:50.127 --> 27:53.460
NOW... the clue to round five

27:53.630 --> 27:55.962
will be waiting for you
in the hotel parking lot

27:56.133 --> 27:59.000
in the car parked
right next to Tommy boy's.

27:59.178 --> 28:02.045
Tick, tick, tick.
Round five's about to start.

28:04.767 --> 28:07.258
Damn it. What am I supposed
to be looking for?

28:07.436 --> 28:09.597
What am I bringing to the parking lot?

28:09.772 --> 28:12.479
Hey, you know, Nick, isn't it funny
how sometimes we can't see

28:12.649 --> 28:14.480
the very thing that will help us,

28:14.651 --> 28:17.518
even though it's staring us
right in the face?

28:23.243 --> 28:24.824
NICK:
Your tattoo.

28:24.995 --> 28:26.610
(HANGS UP PHONE)

28:28.999 --> 28:31.991
- (TOMMY GRUNTS)
- Nice tattoo.

28:32.169 --> 28:34.410
What's your name?

28:35.756 --> 28:37.963
- (WOMAN SCREAMS)
- OK, OK, OK, it's Thomas.

28:38.133 --> 28:41.045
- Tommy Weaver.
- Come on.

28:41.220 --> 28:42.835
Come here. Let's go.

28:43.013 --> 28:45.174
I'm not going anywhere With you, man!

28:45.349 --> 28:49.467
You're coming With me Whether
you want to or not. NOW, get dressed!

28:53.315 --> 28:55.601
- Whoa, Whoa, Whoa...
- Give me that!

28:56.360 --> 28:57.816
Now, come here.

28:57.986 --> 29:00.819
(TOMMY GRUNTING)

29:00.989 --> 29:02.525
(WOMAN SHRIEKS)

29:02.699 --> 29:04.951
- Hey, easy. Easy, man!
- Move!

29:05.119 --> 29:07.826
Hey, baby, do me a favor?
Call the cops.

29:07.996 --> 29:09.952
- Let's go. Come on.
- I had a really good time.

29:10.124 --> 29:12.991
- Hey, easy on me.
- Go!

29:13.168 --> 29:16.285
Really? You want to do this again, huh?

29:16.463 --> 29:19.751
No. I don't. But he does.

29:23.011 --> 29:24.467
(LAUGHS)

29:38.152 --> 29:40.484
(SNIFFS)

29:40.654 --> 29:42.155
(SHOUTS)

29:46.618 --> 29:48.358
(SHOUTS)

29:51.039 --> 29:52.575
(GRUNTING)

30:00.716 --> 30:02.081
(GRUNTING)

30:04.344 --> 30:06.596
(SHOUTS INDISTINCTLY)

30:08.432 --> 30:09.672
(GRUNTS)

30:09.850 --> 30:11.306
Come on!

30:17.941 --> 30:19.101
NICK:
Call the cops!

30:19.276 --> 30:22.143
There's a silver sports car
in the parking lot With a bomb in it!

30:22.321 --> 30:23.686
OK.

30:25.282 --> 30:26.863
Come on! Come on!

30:27.034 --> 30:28.945
Move!

30:32.831 --> 30:34.241
OK, Where's your car?

30:34.416 --> 30:35.405
- My car?
- Yeah.

30:35.584 --> 30:38.417
- My keys are back in the room, genius!
- I don't care Where your keys are!

30:38.587 --> 30:40.919
- Show me Where your car is!
- This beautiful piece of...

30:41.089 --> 30:43.000
Hi, little baby. HOW you doing?

30:43.175 --> 30:45.257
NICK:
Over here. Come on.

30:45.427 --> 30:49.966
- That's my car, man.
- Get in. Stay put.

30:50.849 --> 30:55.092
- But that...
- Yeah.

30:57.689 --> 31:00.226
Hey, that looks like my tattoo.

31:00.400 --> 31:02.777
We're definitely in the right place.

31:02.945 --> 31:04.401
Come on.

31:05.614 --> 31:08.356
- So, what are you looking for?
- I don't know, a clue.

31:08.534 --> 31:11.401
You want a clue? Here's a clue:
you're fuckin' crazy, man.

31:11.578 --> 31:14.365
- A clue to the next round.
- The next round.

31:14.540 --> 31:17.953
- The clue to round five.
- Round five.

31:22.130 --> 31:24.963
Oh, no, no, no, dude,
I am not into that.

31:25.133 --> 31:29.001
Five fingers. Round five.

31:29.179 --> 31:31.170
There's something in here.

31:32.891 --> 31:33.971
What the hell is that?

31:34.142 --> 31:36.133
I don't know,
it looks like coordinates.

31:36.311 --> 31:37.687
Let's see.

31:37.854 --> 31:39.560
Let's see, it's GPS.

31:41.191 --> 31:44.604
Uh... Four-hine-one-two-oh-eight.

31:44.778 --> 31:46.609
One-five-two-eig ht.

31:46.780 --> 31:49.897
Enter. OK, come on. Come on!

31:51.201 --> 31:53.442
Corner of Sherwood and Grant.

31:53.620 --> 31:54.735
Hang on.

31:54.913 --> 31:56.653
Come on. Hey, no, no,
please don't hurt me!

31:56.832 --> 31:58.868
(ENGINE REWING)

32:01.044 --> 32:03.376
OK, let's see it.

32:03.547 --> 32:06.289
All right, I cued it up
to when they find the bike.

32:06.466 --> 32:08.798
MAN:
That's great, this is a lot of help.

32:08.969 --> 32:10.630
MCKENZIE:
Scroll ahead.

32:14.808 --> 32:17.595
Stop. Play it from here.

32:17.769 --> 32:21.102
See, now what kind of an EMT
leaves his patient to take a call?

32:21.273 --> 32:23.605
- Maybe it's important.
- Or convenient.

32:23.775 --> 32:26.107
Stepping out right before it explodes?

32:26.278 --> 32:29.862
- Let's find out who he's talking to.
- Yeah, I'm on it.

32:30.741 --> 32:32.106
MAN:
Well, that's Malloy.

32:32.284 --> 32:35.071
At least now we know who the corpse isn't.

32:35.245 --> 32:37.907
MCKENZIE: Do you see that?
The way he's looking at the camera?

32:38.081 --> 32:41.494
Yeah. That's right, buddy,
smile for the camera.

32:41.668 --> 32:43.499
That's not it.

32:43.670 --> 32:47.254
That doesn't look like someone
who just blew up his own ambulance.

32:47.424 --> 32:50.086
It does if he knows
he's being filmed.

32:50.260 --> 32:52.501
Right there. He did it again.

32:53.388 --> 32:56.471
No, it's like he's looking
at whoever he's talking to.

32:56.642 --> 33:00.510
Like... the camera's watching him.

33:00.687 --> 33:02.803
Check the signal, see if it's being tapped

33:02.981 --> 33:04.721
- by any outside sources.
- Yeah, no problem.

33:05.901 --> 33:08.062
You're serious?

33:08.236 --> 33:10.648
(PHONE RINGING)

33:10.822 --> 33:12.437
One second.

33:14.368 --> 33:15.949
Sykes.

33:18.580 --> 33:19.911
Yeah. We'll be right there.

33:21.249 --> 33:24.833
Someone fitting Malloy's description
just trashed a motel in Chinatown

33:25.003 --> 33:27.460
and abducted one of their guests.

33:28.924 --> 33:30.789
- Nice work.
- Thanks.

33:30.967 --> 33:33.094
OK, here we go.

33:33.261 --> 33:36.424
Monroe, do you want
to get on that? Make the call.

33:45.857 --> 33:50.521
- Look, man, if this is about money...
- Is that what this is about, money?

33:50.696 --> 33:52.527
That is why you kidnapped me, right?

33:52.698 --> 33:54.814
- I didn't kidnap you.
- Really?

33:54.991 --> 33:57.983
That's not what it looks like
from where I'm sitting!

33:59.287 --> 34:00.993
I mean, what other
reason would there be?

34:01.164 --> 34:02.449
I don't know, you tell me.

34:02.624 --> 34:06.867
Wait, wait, I'm supposed to tell you
why you kidnapped...

34:07.045 --> 34:09.582
Look, I didn't want to do any of this.
I didn't have a choice.

34:09.756 --> 34:12.623
- I don't want money.
- Then what do you want?

34:12.801 --> 34:14.007
I don't want anything, all right?

34:14.177 --> 34:16.668
The guy that called your motel room
is behind all of this.

34:16.847 --> 34:19.964
He's already killed one person,
he's threatened my wife,

34:20.142 --> 34:23.726
and he won't stop
unless I play his crazy game.

34:23.895 --> 34:26.272
And what does that
have to do with me?

34:26.440 --> 34:30.649
I don't know yet.
But there has to be a connection.

34:34.322 --> 34:35.607
(BEEPING)

34:35.782 --> 34:38.114
Hey, hold on.
Whoa, whoa, whoa, wait a minute.

34:38.285 --> 34:39.525
You hear that beeping?

34:42.539 --> 34:44.825
- That's my Iocator.
- Locator?

34:45.000 --> 34:47.207
Yeah. I'm on parole, bitch.

34:47.377 --> 34:50.835
Which Ijust violated because of you.
So thanks a lot, asshole.

34:51.006 --> 34:52.587
What are you on parole for?

34:52.758 --> 34:56.125
MAN: Congratulations, Nick.
That's another one in your column.

34:56.303 --> 34:59.511
And we are almost at the halfway point.
Very exciting.

34:59.681 --> 35:02.764
- Who is that?
- Ah! Tommy, Tommy, Tommy.

35:02.934 --> 35:06.472
Welcome to the game.
Now, I am sure your new best friend

35:06.646 --> 35:10.264
has filled you in on the details.
And, Nick, I don't know if you've noticed,

35:10.442 --> 35:13.184
but Tommy is wearing
an electronic tracking bracelet.

35:13.361 --> 35:15.613
Now, because you've been
following the rules,

35:15.781 --> 35:17.521
I'm gonna give you a little help.

35:17.699 --> 35:20.031
I have blocked the signal
to Tommy's anklet,

35:20.202 --> 35:23.160
so the police can't find you... yet.

35:23.330 --> 35:26.493
We wouldn't want to end our fun
so soon, now, would we, boys?

35:26.666 --> 35:31.330
But... let me leave you both
with a little reminder.

35:41.097 --> 35:43.224
(SIREN WAILS)

35:46.770 --> 35:48.226
MCKENZIE:
Are you the lead on scene?

35:48.396 --> 35:50.261
- MAN: Yes, I am.
- What's going on?

35:50.440 --> 35:52.522
(SIREN WAILS)

35:55.904 --> 35:58.395
- In position.
- Yes, sir.

35:58.573 --> 36:01.781
(SIREN WAILS)

36:04.871 --> 36:08.534
We're missing something. We got to be.
He said 12 rounds. Why 12?

36:08.708 --> 36:12.166
- TOMMY: I don't know, man.
- There has to be a connection.

36:12.337 --> 36:14.919
Your anklet, why are you on parole?

36:15.090 --> 36:18.582
It was a... a DUI.

36:18.760 --> 36:20.921
Stupid mistake.
I got out two days ago.

36:21.096 --> 36:22.757
And you don't think
that's a coincidence?

36:22.931 --> 36:25.138
Man, I told you, I don't know
what any of this Shit is about.

36:25.308 --> 36:28.391
- Maybe someone you knew in prison?
- I wasn't in prison, I was in rehab.

36:28.562 --> 36:30.974
- That was money well spent.
- Hey, I was celebrating.

36:31.147 --> 36:34.731
And besides, you don't look like you're
doing too bad, driving a car like this.

36:34.901 --> 36:37.313
Hey, fuck you. This isn't my car.

36:38.321 --> 36:41.779
- Well, whose car is it?
- I don't know.

36:41.950 --> 36:45.238
Why don't you check the glove box,
see if there's any registration in there.

36:50.417 --> 36:54.285
The owner is Roberta Shaw.
Do you know her?

36:54.462 --> 36:56.589
No. You?

36:58.800 --> 37:00.381
Yeah, I do.

37:02.679 --> 37:04.465
That was my lawyer.

37:07.684 --> 37:11.268
Tell me we just got really lucky
and it failed to go off.

37:11.438 --> 37:15.647
It's deactivated. Get this,
Malloy told the clerk about it.

37:15.817 --> 37:17.557
Told him to call the cops.

37:17.736 --> 37:21.320
So we're dealing with the politest
domestic terrorist ever?

37:21.489 --> 37:24.196
Car is registered
to a Donald Perlmutter.

37:24.367 --> 37:27.074
Lives out in the suburbs,
in one of those gated communities.

37:27.245 --> 37:29.236
We're still trying to reach him.

37:29.414 --> 37:31.405
(SIRENS WAIL)

37:32.542 --> 37:34.658
- Hey. Jensen.
- (PHONE RINGING)

37:34.836 --> 37:36.167
- We all set?
- Yeah?

37:36.338 --> 37:38.169
MAN: You were right,
that traffic cam was being tapped.

37:38.340 --> 37:40.422
- By whom?
- Uh, we don't know that.

37:40.592 --> 37:41.581
It's been encrypted.

37:41.760 --> 37:45.969
Yeah, guys, the truth is, this signal's
being rerouted all over the place.

37:46.139 --> 37:49.552
We can't trace it. Whoever's doing this
clearly doesn't want us to find him.

37:49.726 --> 37:53.184
That sound like something
an EMT could do to you?

37:53.355 --> 37:57.769
- Guy's got to have a hobby.
- Figure it out.

38:03.281 --> 38:07.194
Give me that briefcase back there.
It's starting to ring a bell here.

38:07.369 --> 38:08.449
I think I remember...

38:10.580 --> 38:12.741
All right.

38:12.916 --> 38:14.656
TOMMY:
Man, what am I supposed to be looking for?

38:14.834 --> 38:16.210
The scales.

38:16.378 --> 38:18.289
- What?
- The scales.

38:18.463 --> 38:19.669
What about it?

38:19.839 --> 38:22.046
When he first called,
he said something about scales.

38:22.217 --> 38:25.380
That they were out of whack,
and I had to help him rebalance them.

38:25.553 --> 38:27.293
I thought he was rambling.

38:27.472 --> 38:31.181
But, um... maybe not.
Why don't you give her a call.

38:32.185 --> 38:36.098
- Keypad right there, on the dash.
- Yeah, I got it, I got it.

38:36.272 --> 38:38.684
(PHONE RINGING)

38:38.858 --> 38:40.439
- You hear that?
- Yeah.

38:40.610 --> 38:45.695
- Dude, that... that's inside this car.
- Well, find it.

38:48.535 --> 38:50.025
There's nothing here, man.
It's not in here.

38:50.203 --> 38:53.366
- NICK: It's got to be.
- Not... it's not in the car, though.

38:53.540 --> 38:55.496
Hey, hold on.
Whoa, whoa, whoa, wait a minute.

38:55.667 --> 38:57.578
(PHONE CONTINUES RINGING)

39:02.632 --> 39:06.420
- What are you waiting for, man?
- Whoa, whoa. This guy likes bombs.

39:06.886 --> 39:08.547
Trust me.

39:23.611 --> 39:26.148
- (CELL PHONE RINGS LOUDLY)
- Jesus!

39:29.367 --> 39:32.700
MAN: Why is the car stopped, Nick?
What, you decided to quit on me?

39:32.871 --> 39:34.782
- (WHISPERS) You see any cameras?
- What?

39:34.956 --> 39:36.821
Let's look for cameras.

39:37.959 --> 39:40.792
- Where'd you go, Nick?
- NICK: Uh... Kid's got a real small bladder.

39:40.962 --> 39:44.420
- Had to take a piss.
- Hey! Don 't you mess with me, Nick.

39:44.591 --> 39:48.630
I don't care if that kid pisses himself,
you get back in the car.

39:52.057 --> 39:55.675
The kid Malloy took was registered
under the name Iggy Pop.

39:56.936 --> 40:00.303
Yeah, well, it's not exactly
the kind of place you use your real name.

40:00.482 --> 40:02.268
Mmm. Paid in cash, too.

40:02.442 --> 40:04.558
OK, I want to know
everything about Malloy.

40:04.736 --> 40:08.274
See if there's a connection. Some reason
he'd have a grudge against this kid.

40:08.448 --> 40:11.315
- Still think he's innocent?
- Put out an APB on Malloy.

40:11.493 --> 40:14.360
Consider him armed and dangerous.
I want him found.

40:14.537 --> 40:17.529
- Right away.
- See what you can find out about her.

40:17.707 --> 40:19.618
- Get your hands off me.
- Take it easy.

40:19.793 --> 40:21.374
OK.

40:21.544 --> 40:22.704
- You got her?
- I'm ready. Thanks.

40:22.879 --> 40:27.293
SYKES: Uh... l'mjust gonna ask
you a few questions.

40:34.974 --> 40:36.680
Sarah. Oh, my God. Baby?

40:42.357 --> 40:44.769
- (SIGHS) It's not her.
- That's her.

40:44.943 --> 40:46.683
- It's not her.
- That's her.

40:50.115 --> 40:51.446
- NICK: What's going on?
- TOMMY: I don't know.

40:51.616 --> 40:53.527
NICK:
That's a lie. You know something!

40:53.701 --> 40:56.317
This can't be random.
Talk to me. Talk to me!

40:56.496 --> 40:58.703
I don't know, OK?!
I don't know!

40:58.873 --> 41:01.831
I don't have a freaking idea
what's going on right now!

41:02.001 --> 41:04.413
(PHONE RINGING)

41:04.587 --> 41:06.919
MAN:
You like what you see, Nick?

41:07.966 --> 41:10.048
Next time, that could easily be Sarah.

41:10.218 --> 41:14.302
Now, you do as you're told
and get back in the car.

41:14.472 --> 41:16.178
You son of a bitch.

41:16.349 --> 41:20.342
Hey, lmake the rules, you follow.

41:20.520 --> 41:24.058
If people bent the rules to fit
their own needs, there would be chaos.

41:24.232 --> 41:26.223
Laws need to be enforced, Nick!

41:26.818 --> 41:28.900
You're about to find that out.

41:37.704 --> 41:39.990
Go. Get in the car.

41:58.808 --> 42:01.470
SYKES: If it's the best you can do, yeah.
AS long as you've Checked everywhere.

42:01.644 --> 42:02.975
MCKENZIE:
It's right here. All clear.

42:11.154 --> 42:12.940
OK, thanks anyway.

42:14.324 --> 42:16.610
So I had them check
the name the girl gave us.

42:16.784 --> 42:18.740
Tommy Weaver is for real.

42:18.912 --> 42:21.494
At least now we know
who we're looking for.

42:21.664 --> 42:23.404
He's the governor's kid.

42:25.627 --> 42:28.539
Apparently, he's considered
the black sheep of the family.

42:28.713 --> 42:30.920
He's been in and out
of trouble for years.

42:31.090 --> 42:34.127
A real thorn in his
dad's side, politically.

42:34.302 --> 42:35.838
When the governor's ex remarried,

42:36.012 --> 42:39.004
Tommy took her new last name
to piss him off.

42:39.182 --> 42:43.175
Governor pretty much disowned him
after his recent incarceration.

42:43.353 --> 42:46.265
Tommy just got released
from rehab two days ago.

42:46.439 --> 42:49.931
Which is exactly
when the governor went missing.

42:50.109 --> 42:53.567
You think Malloy's involved
in the governor's disappearance?

42:54.447 --> 42:58.281
Well, it's not a coincidence the governor's
grabbed the same day his kid's released.

43:01.120 --> 43:04.738
Check with the rehab facility.
See who Tommy got chummy with.

43:04.916 --> 43:06.531
Maybe he got in deep
with someone he met there.

43:06.709 --> 43:08.916
This is their way of showing
him they're serious.

43:09.087 --> 43:12.079
- (PHONE RINGING)
- Hey, this better be good news.

43:12.257 --> 43:15.420
MAN: Yeah, listen, we pulled a plate
off a traffic cam near the motel.

43:15.593 --> 43:19.085
Malloy left the scene
in a 2012 Mercedes.

43:19.264 --> 43:20.629
MCKENZIE:
OnStar?

43:20.807 --> 43:23.719
No, yeah, we tried, it's blocked,
so we can't trace it.

43:23.893 --> 43:26.726
Also, Tommy's wearing a tracking device.

43:26.896 --> 43:29.512
- That's the conditions of his parole.
- MCKENZIE: Great.

43:29.691 --> 43:32.057
Well, yeah, not really.
We can't trace that either.

43:32.235 --> 43:35.523
Yeah, guys, truth is, this is
unlike anything we've seen before.

43:35.697 --> 43:39.406
This is top of the line stuff,
and it's way above our pay grade, so...

43:40.743 --> 43:43.280
All right. Stay on it.
Call me when you get something.

43:43.454 --> 43:47.288
- MAN: Doing our best.
- (SIGHS) Damn it.

43:49.210 --> 43:52.247
(PAY PHONE RINGING)

43:54.841 --> 43:56.126
(GRUNTS)

43:57.510 --> 43:58.499
NICK:
Come on.

43:59.554 --> 44:01.135
We're here. We're here!

44:01.306 --> 44:04.798
MAN:
That was close, Nick. I was about to hang up.

44:04.976 --> 44:08.594
What, and stop all our fun?
Sounds like you think we're gonna win.

44:08.771 --> 44:13.561
Round six. Hey, we've made it
to the halfway mark. Congratulations.

44:13.735 --> 44:16.351
You know, I have to admit
I thought you'd be dead by now.

44:16.529 --> 44:19.612
- Maybe I was just hoping.
- NICK: Feeling the same way about you.

44:19.782 --> 44:20.988
TOuché.

44:21.159 --> 44:26.370
Now, to win round six, Nick,
you have to figure out its significance.

44:26.539 --> 44:29.121
Why I brought you there.

44:29.292 --> 44:30.782
You wanted to know why you?

44:30.960 --> 44:34.544
Well, Nick... here 's your chance to find out.

44:35.548 --> 44:39.257
I'm giving you the pieces
to the puzzle. Put them together.

44:39.427 --> 44:41.167
You got three minutes.

44:43.097 --> 44:44.962
(NICK SIGHS)

44:45.433 --> 44:48.391
Look around, and see
if you can find a clue. Anything.

44:48.561 --> 44:51.803
- I know this place.
- What'd you say?

44:53.066 --> 44:55.352
I said I know this place.

44:57.403 --> 44:59.519
What do you mean, you know it?

44:59.697 --> 45:03.064
This is the place I had my...
my crash.

45:04.535 --> 45:06.867
The DUI I'm on parole for.

45:09.624 --> 45:13.958
- A year ago?
- Yeah.

45:15.463 --> 45:17.294
I was here, too.

45:18.591 --> 45:21.003
Iwas at...

45:21.177 --> 45:23.543
...the right place at the right time.

45:26.265 --> 45:28.642
This is about that night.

45:30.311 --> 45:32.518
You were the driver.

45:32.688 --> 45:34.519
TOMMY:
l was coming home from a party, man.

45:34.690 --> 45:37.477
I was at a club, and I was...
I was just coming home.

45:42.031 --> 45:44.773
There was a woman
in that car you hit.

45:45.743 --> 45:47.404
She was trapped.

45:50.081 --> 45:51.821
She died.

45:54.168 --> 45:57.752
Wait a minute, that wasn'tjust a DUI.
How are you out?

46:00.091 --> 46:02.173
I told you, man,
it was just an accident.

46:02.343 --> 46:05.335
No, no, no. Bullshit!
Bullshit! That's manslaughter.

46:05.513 --> 46:08.550
How'd a manslaughter charge get reduced
to less than a year in rehab?

46:08.724 --> 46:10.260
Look...

46:11.686 --> 46:13.551
Answer me.

46:13.729 --> 46:16.471
- Answer me!
- It was my dad, OK? My daddy!

46:16.649 --> 46:20.016
He got my charges reduced, OK?
He pulled some strings.

46:20.194 --> 46:23.357
He got a... a good judge,
he hired a great lawyer.

46:23.531 --> 46:26.443
A great lawyer? The dead lawyer
in the back of the trunk?

46:28.953 --> 46:30.659
- Oh, God.
- NICK: This is how the pieces fit.

46:30.830 --> 46:33.196
You, me, the lawyer...

46:37.044 --> 46:38.454
Him.

46:41.132 --> 46:45.000
It was his wife.
You killed his wife, man.

46:45.178 --> 46:46.418
You took something from him.

46:46.596 --> 46:49.383
And rather than pay for what you've done,
you weaseled your way out.

46:49.557 --> 46:51.138
You cheated justice.

46:51.309 --> 46:53.971
Those were the scales
you threw off balance.

46:54.145 --> 46:55.976
Man, this is fucked up.
This is fucked up!

46:56.147 --> 46:58.103
How can a guy just take
the law into his own hands?!

46:58.274 --> 47:00.481
But you could bend it
to avoid paying for your crimes?

47:00.651 --> 47:02.607
You know what they would do
to me in prison?

47:02.778 --> 47:04.109
They'd kill me in a freaking week, man.

47:04.280 --> 47:07.647
At least then you could have
apologized to her in person.

47:08.993 --> 47:12.611
- Yeah.
- It was an accident.

47:12.788 --> 47:15.200
It was a mistake,
the worst mistake of my life.

47:15.374 --> 47:16.875
- Right.
- I didn't do it on purpose, OK?

47:17.043 --> 47:17.998
Is that right?

47:18.169 --> 47:20.034
Am I supposed to just throw away
the rest of my life

47:20.213 --> 47:22.920
because of one really bad choice?

47:23.966 --> 47:28.676
What about the rest of her life?
You ever think of that?

47:28.846 --> 47:31.679
What about the rest of her life?

47:31.849 --> 47:33.464
This is all because of you.

47:33.643 --> 47:37.511
All this Shit that's going on
is because of you.

47:37.688 --> 47:39.770
People are dead because of you!

47:39.941 --> 47:41.522
My partner's barely alive!

47:41.692 --> 47:43.978
My wife's in danger because you...

47:44.153 --> 47:47.236
...you didn't want to pay
for what the fuck you had done!

47:48.324 --> 47:51.487
- You bloodsucker.
- (PHONE RINGING)

47:51.661 --> 47:53.322
Come on.

47:55.915 --> 47:59.658
I got it.
I know what this is about.

47:59.835 --> 48:03.578
It's about that night, the accident,
the one Tommy caused.

48:05.132 --> 48:06.747
You lost your wife.

48:10.096 --> 48:12.212
I lost everything, Nick!

48:12.390 --> 48:15.348
NICK: I'm so sorry. What happened
to her was awful, it's tragic.

48:15.518 --> 48:17.008
- I'm sorry, but...
- Hey!

48:17.186 --> 48:20.144
Don't you dare pretend
you're innocent in all this.

48:21.357 --> 48:23.313
You saved him.

48:24.360 --> 48:27.898
If you had just let him die,
none of this would have happened!

48:28.072 --> 48:30.563
None of this would have been necessary!

48:31.284 --> 48:34.276
She would've had the justice
that she deserved.

48:34.453 --> 48:37.786
But no. No, Nick.
You had to be a hero.

48:37.957 --> 48:39.743
I was doing my job.

48:39.917 --> 48:43.956
Yourjob... was to save her.

48:44.130 --> 48:45.290
The innocent.

48:45.464 --> 48:48.831
Not those who needlessly
inflict suffering and pain!

48:49.010 --> 48:51.626
- NICK: I tried.
- No, you failed!

48:51.804 --> 48:55.388
Twelve jurors were supposed
to decide his fate.

48:55.558 --> 48:59.722
They didn't,
so now I am gonna do it for them.

48:59.895 --> 49:01.806
For all of them.

49:01.981 --> 49:03.312
Round by round!

49:03.482 --> 49:08.852
Him, his rich father,
the judge, the fat-cat lawyer.

49:10.281 --> 49:11.521
You, Nick.

49:15.036 --> 49:16.446
This isn't the answer.

49:16.621 --> 49:20.660
It's the only answer that they're not gonna
be able to buy their way out of, Nick.

49:22.460 --> 49:24.872
Looks like our friend
doesn't want to play anymore.

49:25.046 --> 49:26.786
I think you better get him
back there, Nick.

49:29.800 --> 49:31.586
SARAH:
What do you mean, you can't find him?

49:31.761 --> 49:33.592
Did you try tracking his cell?

49:33.763 --> 49:36.505
We did.
It's not giving off a signal.

49:36.682 --> 49:38.968
Or he removed the batteries
so we can't find him.

49:39.143 --> 49:42.010
That doesn't make any sense.

49:42.188 --> 49:43.803
Is he OK?

49:43.981 --> 49:46.063
We know he was fine
when he left the scene.

49:46.233 --> 49:48.645
And when he abducted the governor's son.

49:48.819 --> 49:51.356
My husband didn't abduct anyone.

49:51.530 --> 49:53.657
(PANTING)

50:01.999 --> 50:04.115
Has he tried to contact you?

50:04.293 --> 50:09.413
No. I haven't heard from him
since he left for work this morning.

50:09.590 --> 50:13.708
Was he maybe acting weird before he left?
Did he say or do anything unusual?

50:13.886 --> 50:16.548
No. Everything was fine.

50:18.224 --> 50:20.055
- Mrs. Malloy...
- (PHONE CHIMES)

50:20.226 --> 50:23.593
...anything you can tell us
about what your husband might be up to

50:23.771 --> 50:26.854
- will only help us find him.
- Look, I'm sorry.

50:27.024 --> 50:31.108
I don't know, but whatever it is,
Nick is not a part of it.

50:31.278 --> 50:33.269
(PANTING, GRUNTING)

50:42.081 --> 50:44.823
Just find my husband?

50:45.000 --> 50:47.252
MCKENZIE:
We'll do our best.

50:48.295 --> 50:50.377
Call me anytime.

50:53.384 --> 50:55.170
(GASPS)

51:03.853 --> 51:06.139
(CRYING)

51:17.408 --> 51:19.774
(PANTING)

51:19.952 --> 51:23.490
(PHONE RINGING)

51:24.290 --> 51:28.454
Looks like you're having trouble
hanging onto your new best friend.

51:28.627 --> 51:32.996
Well, Nick, because of Tommy's antics,
you just lost round seven.

51:33.174 --> 51:35.130
- NICK: No. Wait.
- Too late, Nick.

51:35.301 --> 51:39.135
I just deactivated the block
that was hiding Tommy's anklet signal.

51:39.305 --> 51:41.296
(ANKLET BEEPING)

51:43.350 --> 51:44.681
Oh, shit!

51:44.852 --> 51:46.513
Whoa!

51:46.687 --> 51:50.179
Which means, you have got about
six minutes before every cop

51:50.357 --> 51:52.484
in this city converges on your location.

51:52.651 --> 51:54.903
(PHONE RINGS)

51:55.070 --> 51:57.061
- Hey.
- We've got a trace on Tommy's anklet.

51:57.239 --> 51:59.651
- It's on the west side of the city.
- We're on the west side. Where?

51:59.825 --> 52:00.814
MAN:
Parking garage.

52:00.993 --> 52:04.861
I want every available unit
on those two. Now!

52:05.039 --> 52:08.202
I'd get moving if I were you, boys.

52:09.210 --> 52:12.077
Hey! Hey! Help! Hey, guys!

52:12.254 --> 52:14.586
- What the hell have we got here?
- Help me, please!

52:14.757 --> 52:16.338
- Please, you gotta help me!
- Hey, hey, buddy.

52:16.509 --> 52:17.669
- I'm turning myself in.
- What's the problem?

52:17.843 --> 52:19.174
There's this guy...

52:19.345 --> 52:21.051
Oh, shoot! That's the guy!

52:21.222 --> 52:23.679
NICK:
Officer? Hey, hey, hey, Officer?

52:23.849 --> 52:25.589
- What's going on with this kid?
- I'm not armed.

52:25.768 --> 52:27.804
I won't resist, either,
but you got to listen to me.

52:27.978 --> 52:31.266
- TOMMY: He's trying to kill me!
- Let's get inside the vehicle.

52:31.440 --> 52:33.146
- TOMMY: Now we're going to jail.
- All right?

52:33.317 --> 52:35.228
- Come on, let's go.
- TOMMY: We're going to jail.

52:35.402 --> 52:38.235
- Do you have any weapons on you?
- TOMMY: Oh, shit.

52:39.657 --> 52:40.863
(GRUNTS)

52:46.038 --> 52:47.278
NICK:
No, no, no...

52:47.456 --> 52:49.572
TOMMY:
No, wait...

52:49.750 --> 52:51.365
What are you doing?

52:51.544 --> 52:52.624
Freeze!

53:12.648 --> 53:13.683
NICK:
Tommy!

53:14.859 --> 53:16.474
(GRUNTS)

53:27.496 --> 53:30.203
Ah! Jesus!

53:31.125 --> 53:33.741
- Oh, no, no!
- Come on!

53:36.839 --> 53:37.828
Come on!

53:38.007 --> 53:39.838
(INDISTINCT RADIO TRANSMISSION)

53:40.009 --> 53:42.967
You got to let me go, man. No, please.
You got to let me go, man. You...

53:43.137 --> 53:45.503
Please! You got let me...

53:45.681 --> 53:47.137
Come on, dude!
You got to let me go!

53:47.308 --> 53:48.798
Sorry, guys.

53:50.269 --> 53:51.884
You're part of this,
whether you like it or not.

53:52.062 --> 53:53.643
More lives are at stake here than just yours.

53:53.814 --> 53:56.021
Come on, dude.
Just let me go, all right?

53:57.860 --> 53:59.191
OFFICER:
I'm OK.

53:59.361 --> 54:01.693
- But you're gonna help me.
- Oh, shit. Oh, shit.

54:01.864 --> 54:04.446
(SIRENS WAILING)

54:06.201 --> 54:07.577
OFFICER:
Get out of the car!

54:07.745 --> 54:09.281
Oh, shit.

54:09.455 --> 54:11.946
Put your hands up now!

54:12.124 --> 54:14.740
- Seat belts.
- Seat belts. Definitely seat belts.

54:14.919 --> 54:17.626
(ENGINE REWING)

54:17.796 --> 54:19.878
TOMMY:
Oh... shit!

54:20.049 --> 54:22.085
(TIRES SQUEALING)

54:22.259 --> 54:25.922
- (SIRENS WAILING)
- TOMMY: Wait! You've done this before?

54:28.349 --> 54:29.555
TOMMY:
Go, go, go!

54:31.894 --> 54:32.804
Come on, man!

54:34.313 --> 54:36.349
- Hang on!
- (TOMMY WHIMPERS)

54:36.523 --> 54:37.603
(TOMMY GRUNTS)

54:38.692 --> 54:40.068
What are you doing?

54:40.235 --> 54:42.191
(TOMMY YELLING)

54:43.238 --> 54:46.025
- Calm down.
- Calm down? I'm gonna calm down.

54:46.200 --> 54:48.942
Oh, God! Oh, God! I'm gonna die!

54:53.624 --> 54:54.989
(TOMMY GRUNTS)

54:55.167 --> 54:56.532
(GRUNTS)

54:59.630 --> 55:01.040
- Hang on.
- What?

55:01.215 --> 55:03.376
I don't have anything to hang on to.

55:06.637 --> 55:07.547
Come on, Nick.

55:13.394 --> 55:14.725
Oh, God!

55:15.729 --> 55:17.845
(TOMMY WHIMPERS)

55:20.651 --> 55:21.686
Your anklet...

55:22.027 --> 55:23.187
...we need to kill that signal.

55:23.362 --> 55:26.570
- What?
- Find something to kill that signal.

55:26.740 --> 55:29.607
- (BEEPING)
- Hey, hey, hey.

55:30.911 --> 55:32.276
(CHUCKLES)

55:37.334 --> 55:38.414
(BEEPING)

55:38.585 --> 55:40.792
- (SIRENS WAILING)
- Really?

55:41.630 --> 55:45.088
- Well, fuck, at least I'm trying things.
- You take showers in it?

55:57.896 --> 56:00.228
MAN (OVER RADIO): We've located
the suspect going westbound on 7th.

56:00.399 --> 56:03.106
Stay on it. Don't lose them!
Let's get there.

56:03.277 --> 56:04.733
(TIRES SCREECHING)

56:04.903 --> 56:06.643
(SIRENS WAILING)

56:34.892 --> 56:37.008
(TIRES SCREECHING)

56:39.563 --> 56:40.678
Oh, shit!

56:42.149 --> 56:44.686
Fuck! (GRUNTS)

56:45.360 --> 56:46.645
Show me your hands!

56:48.405 --> 56:49.690
Oh, no.

56:52.826 --> 56:56.569
- Now, step out of the car slowly.
- No.

56:59.374 --> 57:04.914
Come on, buddy. This is stupid.
Just turn yourself in, OK?

57:05.089 --> 57:08.126
You're surrounded!
Step out of the car now!

57:11.386 --> 57:13.468
It can't and now.
This can't and now, man.

57:13.639 --> 57:14.628
What?

57:14.807 --> 57:17.469
- We can't stop now, OK?
- What are you talking about?

57:18.936 --> 57:20.176
(STAMMERING)
What? What?

57:21.355 --> 57:24.142
Oh, man. Oh, no, no, no. What? What?
What are you doing, OK?

57:24.316 --> 57:27.683
- It's just a Taser.
- OK, good. Good, it's just a Taser.

57:27.861 --> 57:29.601
Out of the car with your hands up!

57:29.780 --> 57:32.317
This can't and now. This can't and now.

57:40.207 --> 57:44.075
- What are you doing?
